Declare variables of every scalar type (integer, float, boolean, char).

Create a tuple and access each element by index.

Use an array to store five integers and print them in reverse.

Demonstrate mutability on an integer variable.

Convert an integer to a floating-point value explicitly.

Show type inference on a literal assignment.

Create and use a usize for indexing.

Explain the difference between signed and unsigned integers.

Define and print a Unicode character.

Explain what happens if an integer overflows in debug mode.
